name: Wei Jia Ban Mian Fish Soup 味家板面鱼汤

reviews.text:
I must say this stall has 1 of the best noodles. Tried the Ee-mian Soup and QQ Noodles before, they were really good!

So far the staffs have been really friendly and polite. I find the food reasonably priced too.

Located in spacious coffeeshop. Would return!

Food quality:
Tasty and not too salty nor sweet nor artificial.

Food portion / Price:
Portions are in line with most coffee shop, affordable prices with lots of options at $3.8 or $4.3 unlike many places which charge $5+ or $6+.

Service:
N/A - order, pay and collect.

Crowd:
Some crowd during meal time, wait mainly due to food prep time.

Payment:
SGQR, cash accepted.

This is my go-to Ban Mian place around the area. It is simple, and it is cheap. I usually have the Mee Hoon kueh ($3.30) and sometimes the deep fried dumplings which is not too oily as they drain the oil well. They are 10 for $5. Nice broth for the soup and a good al dente bite for the kueh. They usually open till late. Maybe about 9+ to 10pm. 4 stars because not enough veg usually but I am sure you can always ask for more. The dumplings are a good mix of pork, chives and grated carrots.
